  <notes timestamp="2026-06-02" author="task-execute">
    <summary>
      Wired Zone-B parameterization onto the InsightsIngestRequest record (3 optional
      overrides: PracticeAreaHint, CostCapOverride, Layer2Threshold), added facade-layer
      validation in InsightsOrchestrator.ValidateIngestParameters that runs BEFORE
      delegation to IIngestOrchestrator so bad inputs fail without LLM cost. Tests:
      15 new unit tests covering propagation, defaults, and validation boundaries for
      each parameter.
    </summary>
    <changes>
      <change file="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/PublicContracts/InsightsIngestRequest.cs">
        Extended record with 3 optional parameters per design-a5 §6 parameterSchema:
        PracticeAreaHint (string?), CostCapOverride (decimal?), Layer2Threshold (double?).
        Backward-compatible: existing 3-arg constructor sites continue to compile and
        omit the new fields, which then default to null and trigger the playbook
        parameterSchema defaults downstream.
      </change>
      <change file="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/InsightsOrchestrator.cs">
        Added ValidateIngestParameters internal-static helper. RunIngestAsync now calls
        it after required-field validation, before delegating to IIngestOrchestrator.
        Rules enforced: PracticeAreaHint non-whitespace when supplied; CostCapOverride
        strictly &gt; 0 when supplied; Layer2Threshold finite and in [0.0, 1.0] when
        supplied. NaN + infinities rejected on Layer2Threshold.
      </change>
      <change file="tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Insights/InsightsOrchestratorTests.cs">
        Added 15 new tests in a Wave C5 section covering: full-parameter propagation
        (1), default-null propagation (1), PracticeAreaHint whitespace rejection (2),
        CostCapOverride non-positive rejection (3), Layer2Threshold out-of-range +
        NaN + infinity rejection (6), Layer2Threshold inclusive boundary acceptance
        (4: 0.0, 0.5, 0.7, 1.0). All 42 InsightsOrchestratorTests pass; 28
        ingest-related tests pass repo-wide.
      </change>
    </changes>
    <acceptance-criteria-status>
      <criterion id="all-4-params-accepted-validated-propagated" status="partial">
        Wave C5 implements 3 of the 4 parameters listed in the prompt (PracticeAreaHint,
        CostCapOverride, Layer2Threshold) plus TenantId which is already required on the
        existing contract — total 4 parameters accepted, validated, and propagated to
        IIngestOrchestrator. The "tenantId override" from the prompt is interpreted as
        the existing TenantId field on the request (already required + propagated); no
        new "override" semantic was added because there is no caller-supplied tenant
        identity to override at this layer — the BFF auth filter establishes tenant.
      </criterion>
      <criterion id="each-parameter-effect-verified" status="partial">
        Validation effect verified per-parameter via dedicated unit tests (15 tests).
        End-to-end RUNTIME effect (parameter → playbook node behavior, e.g.,
        Layer2Threshold actually gates the LLM call) is NOT verified at this stage
        because IInsightsAi.RunIngestAsync still delegates to the code-defined
        IngestOrchestrator (Phase 1 implementation). Wave C4 (task 023) rewires
        RunIngestAsync to invoke universal-ingest@v1 via PlaybookExecutionEngine, at
        which point end-to-end effect tests become meaningful and should be added to
        UniversalIngestPlaybookTests (Wave C1 already authored the playbook JSON).
        Caller integration is honest TODAY: callers can pass overrides through the
        stable facade signature; the wire transparently no-ops during the C3-C4 window.
      </criterion>
      <criterion id="x-ai-insights-ingest-header-honored" status="preserved">
        Existing behavior unchanged. This task did not touch the SPE-upload header
        handling. The X-Ai-Insights-Ingest: false override is honored upstream of
        IInsightsAi.RunIngestAsync (in the SPE-upload finalization worker per D-P15-08);
        this task neither suppressed nor modified that path.
      </criterion>
    </acceptance-criteria-status>
    <follow-ups>
      <follow-up wave="C3" task="022">
        Once IngestOrchestrator.cs is retired and Wave C4 rewires RunIngestAsync to
        invoke universal-ingest@v1 via the playbook engine, remove the
        "parameters validated but no runtime effect" caveat from the InsightsIngestRequest
